summary: the more i play blue version the more i realize that my definitions of “Super rare pokemon” (as a kid lol) were because of Gold...
body:
the more i play blue version the more i realize that my definitions of “Super rare pokemon” (as a kid lol) were because of Gold version and how the second half of that game is like backwards blue version.

Like Pikachu you can only get in that one patch of grass down below blackthorn city and Clefairy are in Mt. moon over in kanto.

Like they aren’t really common pokemon in blue, but they aren’t also the “Super rare never encounter” type i always thought they were.
